                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Editorial Note</hi>
                </head>
                <p>The Trusteeship Council resumed its discussion of the Jerusalem question on
                    February 6 and 8. Arab spokesmen objected to the Garreau Plan, which was
                    denounced as cutting Jerusalem to pieces, and called for immediate preparation
                    of the draft statute for the Jerusalem area within the framework of the
                    resolution of December 9. At one point, in answer to the argument that the
                    General Assembly decision for full internationalization could not be
                    implemented, they suggested sanctions as a means of implementation. The Chinese
                    Representative also expressed the view that the Garreau Plan fell far short of
                    the resolution (telegrams 204 and 214, identified also as <gloss
                        target="#t_Tcdel1">Tcdel</gloss> 61 and 66, February 6 and 9, from Geneva,
                    350/2–650 and /2–950).</p>
                <pb facs="0749" n="727" xml:id="pg_727"/>
                <p>A summary of the discussions on February 6 and 8 is printed in <gloss
                        target="#t_TC1">TC</gloss> (VI), pages 109 and 126, each ff.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
